ROAD EXPANSION CORRECTIONS
- Movement acquisition no longer depends only on the final 180 m of a 600 m chunk.
- Current position chunks are considered on every valid location update.
- A 420 m movement lookahead prefetches the travel direction.
- Outer road terminals within 220 m trigger frontier acquisition.
- Internal cul-de-sacs are excluded from outer-frontier detection.
- Moving more than 90 m away from the mapped road network triggers surrounding acquisition.
- Legacy initial fetch-circle assumptions are released unless a chunk is proven by merged graph metadata, cache/integration state, survey data or an explicit empty result.
- Prefetched chunks remain hidden from physical-observation content until the player enters them.
- Movement failures near a frontier or during active movement retry after 45 seconds.
- Survey retry behavior remains unchanged.

